'''Saed Ahmad Salameh Al-Rosan''' ({{langx|ar|سَعْد أَحْمَد سَلَامَة الرُّوسَان}}; born 1 February 1997) is a [[Jordan]]ian professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|center-back]] for [[Jordanian Pro League]] side [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Jordan]], Saed began his career at [[Al-Arabi SC (Irbid)|Al-Arabi]], where he made brief loan stints at [[Al-Ahli SC (Amman)|Al-Ahli]] and [[Al-Sareeh SC|Al-Sareeh]] in 2015 and 2016 respectively. He then departed Al-Arabi on a move to [[Mansheyat Bani Hasan]], lasting two seasons.<ref>{{cite web |title=لقراءة المزيد |url=https://alanbatnews.net/article/240288 |website=alanbatnews.net |publisher=Al-Anbat |language=Arabic |date=26 July 2019}}</ref>

===Ma'an===
On 27 August 2019, Al-Rosan moved to [[Ma'an SC|Ma'an]].<ref>{{cite web |title=معان يقدم لاعبيه الجدد في مؤتمر صحفي |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=844795&pg=1&o=n3132788 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=27 August 2019}}</ref> Al-Rosan impressed with Ma'an in the [[2020 Jordanian Pro League|2020]] season, making him a transfer target for the top Jordanian teams.<ref>{{cite web |title=الروسان يحسم وجهته بعد معسكر النشامى |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1001084&pg=1&o=n3132788 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=8 February 2021}}</ref>

===Al-Hussein===
On 17 February 2021, Al-Rosan moved to [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] for a season.<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يتعاقد مع الروسان |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1003861&pg=1&o=n3132788 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=17 February 2021}}</ref> On 16 January 2022, Al-Hussein renewed Saed's contract for two seasons, after repeated impressive performances for the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يجدد عقد الروسان |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1103142&pg=1&o=n3132788 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=12 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الروسان والكنغولي بادو جديد كرة الحسين اربد |url=https://www.addustour.com/articles/1200123-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D9%86%D8%BA%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%88-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%AF?s=3994946cf78f983aac815b7d2b3e6f8b |website=addustor.com |publisher=Ad-Dustor |language=Arabic |date=18 February 2021}}</ref> On 22 October 2023, Al-Hussein announced through their Facebook account that Saed Al-Rosan suffered a third-degree muscular tear, while on international duty.<ref>{{cite web |title=الإصابة تضرب نجم الحسين إربد |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1279140&pg=1&o=n3132788 |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=22 October 2023}}</ref> On 15 July 2024, Al-Hussein once again announce the renewal of Saed Al-Rosan for two additional years, since regarded as a leader of the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=سعد الروسان مستمر مع الحسين لموسمين جديدين |url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/862023 |website=ammonnews.net |publisher=Ammon News |language=Arabic |date=15 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=الحسين إربد يجدد عقود 3 لاعبين |url=https://m.kooora.com/?n=1341323&o=ncjo |website=kooora.com |publisher=Kooora |language=Arabic |date=15 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Saed Al-Rosan was youth international for Jordan, having first represented the Jordanian [[Jordan national under-23 football team|under-23]] for at the [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship qualification]] process, which took place in Palestine.<ref>{{cite web |title=الجهاز الفني يعلن قائمة منتخب ت 23 للتصفيات الآسيوية |url=https://assabeel.net/news/2017/7/13/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%AA-23-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=assabeel.net |publisher=As-Sabeel |access-date=31 August 2024 |language=Arabic |date=13 July 2017}}</ref> He later participated in the [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship]] itself, which was held in China.

He then represented the [[Jordan national under-23 football team|under-23]]'s cycle once again for the [[2020 AFC U-23 Championship]], which was held in Thailand.<ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الأولمبي يعلن قائمته للاستحقاقات المقبلة |url=https://assabeel.net/news/2019/7/17/%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%ae%d8%a8-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a7%d9%88%d9%84%d9%85%d8%a8%d9%8a-%d9%8a%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%86-%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%a6%d9%85%d8%aa%d9%87-%d9%84%d9%84%d8%a7%d8%b3%d8%aa%d8%ad%d9%82%d8%a7%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%aa-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%85%d9%82%d8%a8%d9%84%d8%a9 |website=assabeel.net |publisher=As-Sabeel |language=Arabic |date=18 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الأولمبي يعلن قائمته لبطولة الصين الرباعية |url=https://assabeel.net/news/2019/10/2/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%A9 |website=assabeel.net |publisher=As-Sabeel |language=Arabic |date=1 October 2019}}</ref>

His first call up for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordanian national football team]] came on 19 June 2021, as a part of preparations to face [[South Sudan national football team|South Sudan]] in the qualifiers for the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=المنتخب الأردني يصل الدوحة لمواجهة جنوب السودان في تصفيات كأس العرب قطر 2021 |url=https://al-sharq.com/article/19/06/2021/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%87%D8%A9-%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%82%D8%B7%D8%B1-2021 |website=al-sharq.com |publisher=Al-Sharq |language=Arabic |date=19 June 2021}}</ref>

Saed scored his first goal for the national team on 26 March 2024, in a 7–0 victory against [[Pakistan national football team|Pakistan]] during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] process.<ref>{{cite web| title=Jordan crushes Pakistan 7-0 in FIFA World Cup Qualifier|url=https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/27-Mar-2024/jordan-crushes-pakistan-7-0-in-fifa-world-cup-qualifier |website=dailypakistan.com |publisher=Daily Pakistan |date=27 March 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Khawaja |first1=Qadir |title=FIFA World Cup Qualifiers: Jordan decimate Pakistan 7-0 |url=https://www.samaa.tv/2087312061-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers-jordan-decimate-pakistan-7-0 |website=samaa.tv |publisher=Samaa TV |date=27 March 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jordan demolish Pakistan 7-0 |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/1172973-jordan-demolish-pakistan-7-0 |website=thenews.com.pk |publisher=The News |date=28 March 2024}}</ref>

